libxcb
------------------------------------------
libxcb provides an interface to the X Window System protocol, which replaces
the current Xlib interface. It has several advantages over Xlib, including:
- size: small library and lower memory footprint
- latency hiding: batch several requests and wait for the replies later
- direct protocol access: one-to-one mapping between interface and protocol
- proven thread support: transparently access XCB from multiple threads
- easy extension implementation: interfaces auto-generated from XML-XCB

Xlib can also use XCB as a transport layer, allowing software to make
requests and receive responses with both, which eases porting to XCB.
However, client programs, libraries, and toolkits will gain the most
benefit from a native XCB port.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.5-1
  libXau6-1.0.5-1
  libXdmcp6-1.0.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.65-1
  automake1.11-1.11.1-1
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.9.89-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.0-1
  libpthread-stubs-0.2-1
  libxslt-1.1.26-1
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10
  python-2.6.5-2
  sed-4.2.1-1
  xcb-proto-1.6-1

Canonical website:
  http://xcb.freedesktop.org/

Canonical download:
  http://xcb.freedesktop.org/dist/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libxcb-1.7-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libxcb-1.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxcb-1.7-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-composite-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-composite0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-damage-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-damage0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-doc-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-dpms-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-dpms0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-glx-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-glx0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-randr-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-randr0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-record-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-record0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-render-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-render0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-res-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-res0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-screensaver-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-screensaver0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-shape-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-shape0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-shm-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-shm0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-sync-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-sync0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xfixes-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xfixes0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xinerama-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xinerama0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xinput-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xinput0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xtest-devel-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb-xtest0-1.7-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxcb1-1.7-X.tar.bz2

Or use 'cygport libxcb-1.7-X.cygport prep' to get a patched 
source directory.

To find out the files included in each binary package, you can
run from the command-line: "cygcheck -l <PKG>".

